Serves: 4-6Ingredients:5ml (1 tsp) smoked paprika5ml (1 tsp) ground cumin5ml (1 tsp) dried garlic flakes or powder5ml (1 tsp) dried oregano2.5ml ( tsp) salt4-6 chicken thighs1 head cauliflower, about 800g, broken into florets50g butter100g Montagnolo Affine* cheese, crumbledSalt and pepper to seasonTonight's supper: Low-carb chorizo & cabbage pieMethod:1) Mix the paprika, cumin, garlic, oregano and salt in a sandwich bag. Place the thighs inside and give it a good shake to coat them. Roast for 30-40 minutes at 190 C until cooked through.2) While the thighs are roasting make the cauliflower mash. Boil the cauliflower florets in salted water for about 20-30 minutes until soft. Drain well and set aside. In the same pot melt the butter, add the cooked florets, then mash with a vegetable masher until finely mashed. Add the cheese and stir to melt . Adjust the seasoning to taste and keep warm.3) Take the chicken out of the oven and rest for 5 minutes. Place on top of the of the mash, drizzle some pan juices over it and serve immediately with steamed broccoli on the side. - Recipe by heinstirred.com*Montagnolo Affine is a triple-cream, semi-soft, full-fat white mould cheese which combines the texture and rich taste of brie with a distinctive bite of blue cheese. Available at Woolworths.